Request Validation:
- Verify software is on approved software list
- Confirm manager approval if required
- Check license availability
- Verify system meets minimum requirements

Pre-Installation Checks:
- Confirm user's device make/model and OS version
- Check available disk space
- Verify administrative access method (remote tools, local admin)
- Ensure no conflicting software is installed

License Management:
- Reserve or assign license from license pool
- Document license assignment
- Record license key or activation method
- Update license tracking system

Installation Process:
- Connect to device via remote management tool
- Download software from approved source
- Run installation with appropriate parameters
- Enter license key or activate via volume licensing
- Complete installation wizard

{% if software_type == 'office' %}
Microsoft Office Installation:
- Install via Microsoft 365 portal or SCCM
- Sign in with user's Microsoft 365 account
- Verify all required Office apps are installed
- Configure default file save locations
{% endif %}

{% if software_type == 'specialized' %}
Specialized Software:
- Follow vendor-specific installation guide
- Configure required integrations
- Set up database connections if needed
- Apply any required patches or updates
{% endif %}

Post-Installation:
- Launch application and verify it opens correctly
- Complete initial configuration if needed
- Apply latest updates/patches
- Configure user preferences if required

Documentation:
- Update software inventory
- Record installation in asset management
- Provide user with quick start guide if available
- Close ticket with installation confirmation
